    Atomask
    3.0 out of 5 starsGood basic digital watch for women
    July 6, 2016
    Color: Black/Gray StripeVerified Purchase
    Okay, so it's a great watch for women with small to medium wrists. Here's my pros and cons list:

    Pros:

    - Super easy to set. The package insert does NOT include instructions. This is my first Timex Expedition watch, so I had not experience going in. All you do is press Set and you use the Start and Stop buttons to move up and down, respectively, through the settings. Easy enough!

    - I love the simplicity of the watch. It's simple and easy to read.

    - It has the day of the week AND the month AND the date. I wanted to make sure any watch I get has these features.

    - The watch band seems high quality. It is fabric/nylon, so it should hold up for several years (we'll see I guess).

    - The Indiglo is pretty and works great in the dark!

    Cons:

    - I have to tighten the band as tight as possible in order to prevent the watch from wobbling around my wrist. It may be because my wrist is small and the watch itself is a bit heavy in comparison. I AM new to wearing a watch (last time I wore one I was very young), so maybe it's just something I have to get used to.

    - The display is perfect, but only when looking at it straight on (when facing you directly). If you were to, say, glance over at your watch while you're typing on your computer, you can't see the time. It's too blurry. So the viewing angles are terrible. You can only see the time if you look directly at it. Again, this might be an issue with all digital watches, but I sort of expected more in today's technological world. This is probably my biggest con and biggest disappointment.

    - The band holder is also nylon, so I had some trouble getting the extra band into the band holder. Now that I think more about it, I'm not sure what a better alternative would be for a nylon band... maybe if they glued the band holder on to the band, it wouldn't move around so much when trying to insert the band into the holder. Once you're inserted it, it seems to stay in place, though. So that's good. But I can see it loosening up and not working well in the future.

    I've only had this watch since yesterday, so I haven't been able to test its waterproofness yet. I will update this review if I am unhappy with the waterproofness.

    Overall, it's exactly what I was looking for: a basic digital watch that shows the day and date, with a band that is small enough to fit my female wrist. However, I would have liked it better if the price was $10-15 less than what I paid for it.

    5.0 out of 5 starsGoing and going and going and going
    October 29, 2018
    Color: PlumVerified Purchase
    I have had nothing but Expeditions for nearly 20 years. I remember the first one was an aqua color and I was almost in a panic to get a replacement when it just became too dysfunctional from me wearing it constantly - to bed - in the shower - kayaking - yard work - you name it, it was with me.
    In this picture, the watch on the left is the one being replaced by the one on the right. It's hard to believe that the old one is nearly 10 years old with only one battery replacement and has had a few trips through the washer AND dryer, it's been dropped, sat on, frozen, slopped with paint and cleaned, raked across a tree trunk (which saved my wrist from major damage,) and various other forms of abuse, none of which I recommend of course.
    The price is right, the band is indestructible, it's so easy to set, and the indiglo lights up the numbers and not the background so it's easy to see.

    Expat Family
    5.0 out of 5 starsPerfect for a Growing Boy- Smaller face, tough, and a few other points.
    February 23, 2015
    Color: Black/RedVerified Purchase
    My son loves this watch. We looked and looked and finally settled on this Timex Expedition Mid-Size- it was perfect for our 10 year old son. We went through a couple iterations of "kids" watches and they just didn't last. This watch has held up through swimming, basketball, baseball, and general rough housing without a scratch.
    - This is a good looking watch that is not too big on my son, or my wife who borrows it on occasion.
    - Built like an "adult" watch vice the child watches we had tried in the past.
    - Easy to read with a backlit face to make it easy at night.
    - Intuitive settings- my son can set and change the alarms and the time zone on his own.
    - The band is tough and soft- very comfortable with a Velcro strap that is easy to get on and off and to adjust.

    Very happy with the purchase and my son really appreciates adult features and design in a "kid" sized watch.

    dandeliongirl
    4.0 out of 5 starsGreat watch, but band is tight fit for average sized woman’s wrist
    July 27, 2018
    Color: Blue/BlackVerified Purchase
    I read reviews before purchasing, and noticed many reviewers commented on the small size of the watch. I purchased anyway, because I have small to average sized wrists. Ended up giving to a family member because it was a very tight fit for me. If wanted to wear the watch more loosely than intended, then most of the visible portion of the band would be the grey Velcro portion of the strap, with only a small portion of the pretty grosgrain ribbon visible. It would have been possible to wear this way, but the rubbery “tab” on the end of the band isn’t as flexible as the fabric portion of the band and didn’t bend well over the curve of my wrist, so the band felt very uncomfortable, even when adjusted to a larger size.

    I have never experienced fit issues with bracelets or ladies’ watches before purchasing this watch- for instance, with metal link watches, I’ve always had to remove several links to make them fit, so that’s why this was surprising. The band itself is lovely, but just didn’t work well for me. So, if your wrist measures 6 inches or less, this might work well for you. Otherwise, I don’t think this will be the one for you, either!
